<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-25T07:21:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-25T07:21:00-05:00" n="163" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 T 71/155: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Helsingfors</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Haynes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Helsingfors</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-25T14:00:00+01:39"><hi rend="italic">April 25,
                                        1919, 2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:52
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>254. <persName>Tredwell</persName> with twenty-one others leaving Moscow.
                            Expected to arrive Finland few days.<note n="48" xml:id="d163fn48">Consul <persName>Tredwell</persName> crossed the frontier into
                                Finland Apr. 27.</note> I will either go to border or ask
                                <persName>Imbrie</persName> meet him and facilitate journey to
                            Helsingfors. Not sent Paris.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Haynes</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>